  _id: theo
  _characterName: Theo
  _role: Trader / market access
  _age: Late thirties
  _home: Theo's wagon and the road
  _work: Trade, market orders, and wagon routes
  _keepsake: Trade ledger
  _tagline: The worldly trader who can price a mushroom, a story, and an open road.
  _leadParagraph: Theo is a well-groomed traveler with a trim beard, a better coat
    than most Hollowfen villagers, and a ledger never far from hand.
  _backgroundParagraph: His wagon gives Wren access to buyers beyond the village
    and turns unusual mushrooms into a trade that can survive the axle ruts.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Theo prefers an honest bargain because it saves time. He
    sees opportunity quickly and is careful to name the cost when it matters.
